==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pash
<hw>Pash</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Prob. of imitative
origin, or possibly akin to <ets>box</ets> to fight with the
fists.]</ety> <def>To strike; to crush; to smash; to dash in
pieces.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <au>P. Plowman.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧I'll
<xex>pash</xex> him o'er the face.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pash
<hw>Pash</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot., the pate. Cf. <er>Pash</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The head; the poll.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧A rough <xex>pash</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A crushing blow.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A heavy fall of rain or snow.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pasha</ent>⟦br⟧
